A fire broke out at Stellenbosch University's Huis ten Bosch women's residence on Monday night, the university's spokesperson said. "As far as we know, all of the students were evacuated," said Martin Viljoen. The residence usually accommodates 164 students. UPDATE | Student treated for burns as Stellenbosch University res fire contained Viljoen said the fire is understood to have started at around 19:30. The cause of the fire is not yet known. The university plans to find alternative accommodation for the students, and will offer counselling. This is a developing story.  Stellenbosch university Huis ten Bosch residence on fire. (Picture supplied) GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 